<!--DOCTYPE section SYSTEM "file:/opt/share/xml/Oxygen/docbook/dtd/docbookx.dtd"--><ns6592:section xmlns:ns6592="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.vi.modes">

  <ns6593:title xmlns:ns6593="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The modes of Vi</ns6593:title>
  <ns6594:para xmlns:ns6594="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    When working with <ns6595:emphasis xmlns:ns6595="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vi</ns6595:emphasis> you are either in one of 2 modes, 
    <ns6596:emphasis xmlns:ns6596="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">command mode</ns6596:emphasis> or <ns6597:command xmlns:ns6597="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">input mode</ns6597:command>.
  </ns6594:para>
  
  <ns6598:section xmlns:ns6598="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns6599:title xmlns:ns6599="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The command mode</ns6599:title>
    <ns6600:para xmlns:ns6600="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      To switch to command mode, press <ns6601:command xmlns:ns6601="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">&lt;Esc&gt;</ns6601:command>.
      Command mode enables you to
      <ns6602:itemizedlist xmlns:ns6602="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns6603:listitem xmlns:ns6603="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6604:para xmlns:ns6604="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          navigate through your document, even with keyboards which have no arrow keys,  
        </ns6604:para></ns6603:listitem>
        <ns6605:listitem xmlns:ns6605="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6606:para xmlns:ns6606="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          enter one of a wide variety of commands,  
        </ns6606:para></ns6605:listitem>
        <ns6607:listitem xmlns:ns6607="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6608:para xmlns:ns6608="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          or visually mark aspects of the document from visual mode (see
          <ns6609:xref xmlns:ns6609="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.platforms.linux.vi.visualMode"/>).
        </ns6608:para></ns6607:listitem>
      </ns6602:itemizedlist>
      In addition to the editing commands, you can also enter any shell command from
      <ns6610:emphasis xmlns:ns6610="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vim</ns6610:emphasis>'s command mode via
      <ns6611:cmdsynopsis xmlns:ns6611="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
<ns6612:command xmlns:ns6612="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">:!&lt;shellCommand&gt;</ns6612:command>
      </ns6611:cmdsynopsis>
      like, for example,   
      <ns6613:cmdsynopsis xmlns:ns6613="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
<ns6614:command xmlns:ns6614="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">:!ls</ns6614:command>
      </ns6613:cmdsynopsis>
      if you want to see a directory listing of the current directory.
    </ns6600:para>
  </ns6598:section>
  
  <ns6615:section xmlns:ns6615="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns6616:title xmlns:ns6616="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">The input mode</ns6616:title>
    <ns6617:para xmlns:ns6617="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The input mode lets you edit the document. It has itself again 3 submodes:
      <ns6618:orderedlist xmlns:ns6618="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns6619:listitem xmlns:ns6619="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6620:formalpara xmlns:ns6620="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns6621:title xmlns:ns6621="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Insert mode</ns6621:title>
          <ns6622:para xmlns:ns6622="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            <ns6623:emphasis xmlns:ns6623="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vim</ns6623:emphasis> provides a number of ways to enter the insert mode
            (see <ns6624:xref xmlns:ns6624="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.platforms.linux.vi.inserting"/>). 
            The most common are <ns6625:command xmlns:ns6625="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i</ns6625:command> to insert infront of the cursor
            and <ns6626:command xmlns:ns6626="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">a</ns6626:command> to insert after the cursor.
          </ns6622:para>  
        </ns6620:formalpara></ns6619:listitem>
        <ns6627:listitem xmlns:ns6627="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6628:formalpara xmlns:ns6628="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns6629:title xmlns:ns6629="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Virtual replace mode</ns6629:title>
          <ns6630:para xmlns:ns6630="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            This mode is only available with <ns6631:emphasis xmlns:ns6631="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vim</ns6631:emphasis>, not with <ns6632:emphasis xmlns:ns6632="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Vi</ns6632:emphasis>.
            It does a  virtual replace on the screen buffer, but to a large extend simulates an overwrite mode.
            To enter the virtual replace mode, use the command
            <ns6633:cmdsynopsis xmlns:ns6633="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns6634:command xmlns:ns6634="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
gR              
            </ns6634:command></ns6633:cmdsynopsis>
          </ns6630:para>
        </ns6628:formalpara></ns6627:listitem>
      </ns6618:orderedlist>
      To leave any of these input modes, you press <ns6635:command xmlns:ns6635="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Esc</ns6635:command>. You
      will be back in command mode.
    </ns6617:para>
  </ns6615:section>
  
</ns6592:section>